Distribution.
Parotocinclus pentakelis
is known from two localities of the Rio Tocantins basin ( Fig. 4 ). The type-locality is at Rio Palmas (
12 o 48’ 05” S
;
46 o 28’ 38” W
), municipality of Lavandeira, southeastern of Tocantins state . The new species is also found in a second locality at Rio Manuel Alves da Natividade (
11 o 36’ 41” S
;
47 o 02’ 39” W
), a river draining directly to Rio Tocantins , municipality of Porto Alegre do Tocantins .
